Only pages identified as SCANNED by Layer 1 are processed.
Native pages are left unchanged.

==========================================================
PREPROCESSING PIPELINE
==========================================================

Implemented image preprocessing using OpenCV.

Processing steps:

1. Download page image from MinIO

2. Decode image bytes into an OpenCV image

3. Convert image to grayscale

4. Apply Gaussian Blur to reduce image noise

5. Correct small page rotations (deskew)

6. Apply Otsu thresholding to obtain a clean
   black-and-white image

7. Encode the processed image as PNG

8. Replace the existing page image in MinIO
   with the preprocessed version

